The paper introduces a framework for updating knowledge bases represented by extended disjunctive programs, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and logic programming (cs.AI, cs.LO). The paper also discusses different types of updates, including view updates and theory updates, which are related to database management (cs.DB). The use of abductive programs and logic programming procedures also suggests a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
